caption: Love this place. It's always great. I have so many favorite items it's hard to pick what to order. Basically, whatever you get, you can't go wrong. Among my favs are the mock eel, eggplant, radish cake, Dan Dan noodles, shrimp toast, soup dumplings and a new one I just discovered - sesame you yu squid dish. Cocktails go great with the food. All around one of the best restaurants
Had THE best time here! The soup dumplings (amongst other things) are unbelievably delicious and the service (Nisha is fantastic!!!) is wonderful. I would love to come here with a big group.
Great vibes, especially the outdoor patio in the back. Highly recommend the dan dan if you appreciate spicy food paired with the layover cocktail.
Recommended
yum!
Was super excited about the menu. Looked killer.  Sadly Food was not outstanding.  Total disappointment.  Not bad.  Ok. Just not good.
So delicious. Best food I've had in a long time.

The mock eel was surprisingly delicious. I HATE mushrooms, but it didn't feel like i was eating any. 5/5  The green beans were incredible too. 5/5  Finally we tried the Kung Po chicken which was really disappointing. The dish was good, but it was like 10% chicken and 90% veggies/sauce. It was really disappointing as I thought I'd get a lot of chicken to share, but it was barely anything.
Tried this place once with my friend and I am obsessed ever since. I enjoy the good mood and delicious dishes and beverages. Great work.
Great food! Really makes you smile
Delicious food, amazing ambiance, fabulous service.
Excellent, also great vegetarian options
Great food, great atmosphere!
Great backyard space for outdoor dining. Great service and food.
Super delicious and classic Chinese food. No fuss, all flavor and quality. Had the pea shoots and eggplant and it was excellent. If they’re on DeliverZero I’d definitely order all the time!
So delicious! So fresh!  Many nice vegetarian options.  The staff is friendly and helpful.

This place really is great! The staff is super friendly and lovely to deal with. The food has a depth of flavor that keeps us coming back. Overall this is an amazing spot for Chinese and I highly recommend a trip! :)
I think about the dry fried long beans often...and the soup dumplings. So good.

In person this place is AWESOME. The dumplings are great and the vegetable dishes are delicious. It’s a lovely space and the staff are really kind and accommodating. However, for delivery it’s pretty abysmal. I’ve ordered several times and I have to give up at this point. It’s somewhat far from me so I don’t expect perfection, but in a recent order the dumplings were falling apart from sitting and the kung pao chicken was soggy (they use the inferior method of breading it vs just cornstarch marinade). The sesame noodles were perfection, which gives you a small window into how good they normally are. Also, it’s relatively expensive and they don’t provide rice. New dumplings are way too big vs old dumplings. Basically pork hockey pucks. I love you kings co but I’ll see you when covid is over. If you do get delivery, the veg dishes, the mapo tofu and the sesame noodles travel well.
You cannot go wrong with anything on the menu! The staff is very knowledgeable about the ingredients and flavor profiles. If they have a special, get it!
Just stellar. Some of my favorite Chinese food in the city! I recently ordered takeout and got the Mapo Dofu, Ants Climbing a Tree noodles.

We ordered Christmas dinner from them in an effort to stay comfortable Christmas 2020 and to support local businesses. It was a fantastic decision- I’m posting the menu they had special for Christmas. It was so delicious and their staff had a great team effort going on to get the orders out. Indoor dining is still closed and it doesn’t have the real estate for outdoor dining. What ever you order, these guys in Williamsburg are sure to please!
The best restaurant in Brooklyn

Just stellar. Some of my favorite Chinese food in the city! I recently ordered takeout and got the Mapo Dofu, Ants Climbing a Tree noodles, and Chop Your Head Off soup, and I would absolutely order every dish again. I was in heaven! The portions were large enough for leftovers too.

I loved the food here. I ordered steamed Shanghai Bok Choy and Kung PO chicken. It was so tasty and spicy.  I tried rice beer which was very good. The ambience was great. The servers were very friendly. I would definitely recommend this restaurant.
Great food, nice servers

We have been coming here to eat bok choy potstickers and gulf shrimp & choy. It has been amazing until today, not sure what happened but dumplings were not fresh, tasted very different and chewy. We weren’t told about change in menu in shrimp, it never came breaded before and bok choy was overcooked. Unfortunately we had food to go so weren’t able to go back to change it as we live far away. Disappointing since we drove far to get it.

I've eaten here and it was very good, so I don't want to give them the minimum rating, but my online delivery experience has been terrible.  More than once my order was canceled with no explanation, most recently more than 90 minutes after it was placed.  I'm grouchy and hungry with few options because of door dash.  If you can go to the restaurant in person I'd highly recommend it.
Delicious food, nice atmosphere and good service
We just referred to this as one of the best meals we’ve ever eaten. Totally worth it 1000% :)
All....the....flavors! So great! Drinks are awesome too.  My favorite: Hong Kong Style Noodles and Mock eel!

Been here once and maybe ordered the wrong things but left not loving it. I remember it being too spicy and salty. Since covid, have ordered a couple times and everything has been amazing. Love the dim sum approach, order a bunch of things and share because there are so many great dishes to try. Get the greens beans and shrimp toast, you won’t be disappointed, and wash it down with a mai tai.
The soup dumplings were amazing. The outdoor seating is quaint and the service was good.
thank GOD for this place. dandan mian and kung po chicken are the best in the city.
I can't tell you how much I love showing off that this restaurant delivers to our place to guests.
I'm in love with the ribs and fried rice!
TASTY food, good vibes, good people, the garden is nice place to catch up and chill... it’s best if you come super early because tables get busy very quickly.
Best dumplings. 🥟
Best restaurant in Williamsburg. If you want an out of body experience, order the soup dumplings. They are heaven.
The service was great and we loved everything we ordered! The buns were definitely our favorite though. Would highly recommend this spot!
Out of this world amazing food with nice service and good cocktails. Try the mock eel!
The best soup dumplings you will ever have.
Food was really good, try the steamed buns(amazing).

The service is good. The food is fantastic with great flavors. Cute little spot in Williamsburg. Overall, it's just really good food. The wok seared long dumplings are different but so good and great for sharing (you get 4).The dan dan mian was actually spicy so that was a nice and delicious surprise.
Delicious food and great service! I’ve dined in and ordered take away, both were excellent.
(Translated by Google) Best Dan Dan noodles!  (Original) Best Dan Dan noodles!
My favorite restaurant in Williamsburg. We had the chop your head off soup, General Tsos, and the hanging pork fried rice most recently. It was on point as always.

First experience was amazing. Food is excellent and huge portions. We arrived too late for our reservation and the host still did an amazing job at not only finding us a table but also handling resy cancelation fees. Incredible A+ guys we will be back !
Very disappointed in the ribs

Excellent food, with some heat to it (oyster mushrooms are phenomenal). Great tiki inspired drinks. The garden in the back is quiet and very cozy with real grape vines all around you. Friendly attentive staff. A must go in the area.
Get the egg rolls or live your entire life not knowing pure bliss.
Good eats and there outdoor seating deff a nice place to go for dinner

Wow! Everything - the fried oyster mushrooms, the red chili squid, the smoked tofu in the fried rice - simply divine! The food was fresh and flavorful. The outdoor dining area in the back is sunny with the perfect amount of shade, and the grapevines are gorgeous. This was my first time dining at a restaurant since February - thank you for making this experience so memorable with your amazing food (and kind server)!
Food is overpriced, only food that was good was the fried appetizers. My father and I both had meals so salty it was burning our mouths we couldn't finish it. IF you eat here ask for low SALT!
Probably some of the best Chinese I've ever had.  The drinks are nothing special and its hard to get a table but well worth the wait.
My wife and I love their food. Always fantastic quality and service when we went. We recently had delivery and it was just as good as it is in the restaurant.

Definitely a high-end Chinese restaurant. Prices were on the higher side, however, the food was very flavorful and delicious. My husband and I got two dinner dishes and the dumplings which cost $60+ with tax and delivery. Would definitely order from here again because of the quality, but would not be an everyday thing because of the cost.

This food tastes sterile. A strange, sauceless imitation of Chinese food. Upon pickup their attitudes were great but I wish the food was the same. General tsos chicken was NOT the way to go as it was drier than the Sahara's toe crease, lacked any flavors reminiscent of real Chinese food, and overall was a major disappointment in my life. The Kung Pao chicken was uninspiring and did nothing for anyone. The pork fried rice deserved a better home though like in some hot sauce. Shout out to Brooklyn. We shall banish this place to the seasoning aisle where it can seek its soul...

An AMAZING dining experience. Get a reservation as it fills up very quick. Nothing on the menu disappoints, flavors are robust but not overwhelming. This is a place where it's great to go with a group and order everything on the menu to share. The interior itself is amazing, luscious red tones and leather booths.

Thoughts out to our favorite restaurant during these trying times. They have the soup dumplings on Caviar, which are typically only an eat in dish and to die for. Cold sesame noodles, dried fried long beans and salt & pepper veal short ribs are incredible. No bad dish on the menu.  Please order and support our neighborhood gem!
Tasty

Fantastic food, cocktails, beer and service. Slightly weird the two of us had to sit slightly awkwardly at the bar rather than at free tables. Superb soup dumplings, green beans and terrific cold sesame noodles.
I love this place. Super solid. Super true to the flavor. Amazing interior. It's busy, but that's what you get when you have a bomb restaurant. Highly recommend.  I dream about the mock eel.
Not authentic

Went for dinner, as soon as I walked in server asked if I was there for a pick up order. I don’t want to be offended, but not every brown guy is there for a pick up. I said no and went to the host, she was sweet. Didn’t eat here, probably will never come back.
(Translated by Google) Vien  (Original) Vien

Yes, it’s not authentic Chinese. Yes, the decor is like an American pastiche of what a movie Chinese restaurant would look like. Yes, it is pricier than comparable Chinese owned places. But the food, oh the food is so good. The house soy sauce, the spring rolls, the dumplings, the beef and broccoli, the Kung Pao chicken, the mock eel (one of the best mock meats I’ve ever had). The drink menu is also always sure to please, with Asian flavors that make them unique spins on more classic cocktails. It might not be the best place for authentic value Chinese food, but the ambiance, service, presentation - everything is designed to impress. And impress it does.
Cosy ,warm and welcoming place . Great food cocktails and great service .
Mmmmmmmm delicious. Gets busy but well worth the wait. Some of the best Chinese in the city. Everything we have tried is delicious. Must try the pork soup dumplings. Nice cocktails too :)
The staff here are literal angels!!!!!!

BEWARE!!!!! I got severe food poisoning here (as did the entire table)... we ordered the soup dumplings and a variety of noodle dishes... everything tasted great at the time, then came home and was destroyed for days. NEVER eating there again!!! Stay far far far away!!

Kings County Imperial serves dishes from multiple regions of China, including both Canton and Sichuan. But no only that now you can learn all you need know to make delicious #dumplings from scratch in a #handson class led by Chef and owner Josh Grinker.
Excellent though far for us to get to.
Awesome

I ordered the Copper Well and the Shrimp toast. The food had a great portion and the copper well wasn't oily at all. I think the shrimp toast was an amazing appetizer. The people there were nice. I'll come back and try something new next time.

Dependable, and still trendy considering how hard it is to get a table. We got there right after opening on a Saturday night and were able to get a table for 6. Great option for sharing plates. Interesting cocktails.
(Translated by Google) Very nice  (Original) Muy agradable

This place is awesome. The soup dumplings were delicious definitely a great appetizer. The Crispy Garlic Chicken was fresh tasty and delicious. The Angry Pork Fried rice was amazing. The Pineapple Tonic and the Shanghai Mule were great cocktails. Giving the restaurant a 5 star review.
Be careful when ordering take-out or delivery, they don’t serve rice with their entrees.
Get multiple orders of the green beans.
Awesome food and drinks!

Their pork soup dumpling special was delicious, on par with Chinatown dumpling joints. Perhaps, if I had to be picky, the wrapper was a bit thick, not allowing for as much soup on the inside - but the soup was yummy, the pork filling was of good quality and perfectly salty.  Their mushu vegetable with tea smoked duck was very disappointing. The vegetable was surprisingly flavorless and the pancakes were soggy (as in possibly not fully cooked) and served TORN! They are supposed to be served slightly crispy (or just cooked properly), making the creation of a mushu possible. The duck was mixed into the veggies in an unloving manner. The plum sauce was presented as hoisin sauce making me question either ingredient choices of the restaurant or the server's knowledgeability. Hoisin is still super tasty and a fine alternative, but if you're gonna bring mushu to town, it's gotta be with the PLUM sauce!  Also, this is a minor incident but the attitude/service was lacking: our table was rocking big time. We requested a table wedge to keep it from rocking. The server pointed us to the floor saying, "There's one down there some where." Were we supposed to use our ready-to-munch hands on the ground and find a dark piece of rubber in the dark?? She walked away leaving us confused and came back in a bit with a wedge. Yay, she helped us - but with some 'tude. No thanks!

Great place for chinese food. I suggest the green beans! The restaurant is vegan friendly which makes it easier to go to with all different friends. If you go during the happy hour, its $15 per person and you get a ton of food ( I think before 7??). If you can go early, do it! Great food at a great price

Portions are served family style and were large enough that two people split one soup and one entree and walked away full. Egg drop soup- excellent! Sacha beef and Chinese broccoli- fantastic! For the amount of patrons in the restaurant (near capacity) our meals came out quickly.
Lots of veggie options! The king oyster "calamari" was out of this world 🤤😍

Absolutely amazing food. The Long Dumplings and Hong Kong needles are some of my favorites. They also have very good specialty drinks. Male a reservation before going. They get very packed and it is a small space. But cozy, comfortable, incredible staff, and amazing food if I haven't already mentioned!

This is my go-to local neighborhood GEM.  The vibe here is intimate and discreet - great date night spot but has big tables to easily host a group of 6+ (with resos planned well ahead).  Must try their famous mock eel app, soup dumplings and very spicy Dan Dan noodles (I give those three plates five stars all the way).  The drinks here are crafted amazingly and the beats are always on point. Great little spot that I wish wasn't so full 90% of the dinner time.
5-7pm is dimsum special time. Really worth it!
Way off last night. Everything was overspiced with heat, garlic and smoke. Nothing was consistent with its namesake in Brooklyn,  which is about 500x better.

Cute place with a nice atmosphere. Unfortunately the dishes were very hit and miss. The lotus root salad was severely lacking in black vinegar and flavour in general but the long beans were tasty and authentic. A place to go if you know what’s good beforehand.
Dumplings on point

We participated in their first ever pig roast. It was delicious. For only $50 per person, we got all you can drink beer and wine, chicken dumplings, cold sesame noodles, and make-your-own buns with the roasted pork. The food was great and the new backyard and event space was great. They also had a DJ during the event, which was fun. I will definitely plan on attending future pig roasts.

Best fried rice I've ever had. I got the fried rice with tofu as a takeout order and it was fantastic. If all Chinese food tasted like this, I would never again find myself saying "I don't like Chinese food." My foodie boyfriend had dim sum and he described it as "a joy." I've never heard him describe food like that and he really likes food.

We arrived at this place for lunch. my friend recommended this place.  Well, it was very nice. the staff members were so friendly and we had a great feeling. The food was just great. We enjoyed every moment and we will definitely return to this restaurant. Warmly recommended.

Excellent Chinese Food. A cut above the average.  If you love Chinese food you will just love Kings County Imperial...!  Hot & Sour soup unlike any I've had anywhere, Including New York, San Francisco, Hong Kong and Taiwan! The Soup dumplings will leave you breathless and the Pork Buns were so, so soft and tasty, covered with a delicate Plum Sauce to die for.  The pork and Beef dishes were so tender and juicy and served with micro greens that burst into so many flavors with each bite.  If you're craving Chinese you must go th Kings Count Imperial. A not so flashy but very comfy environment to dine on the most succulent Chinese food this side of the Orient...!
Some of the best or the best Chinese food I've had in my life. So so so good. I'll be back in a few days...
One of the best meals I have had in awhile. Fantastic food, great environment and friendly staff.
The absolute best !!!! Great bar and drinks and there isn't one bad thing on the menu. Always really packed. Small space

comparing it with the Sichuan food in the near neighborhood, the menu was too much (too many choices) which as a result the food came out slightly above mediocre. The atmosphere and decor is beautiful, we came in right at opening hour with no reservation so luckily didn’t have to wait. But, generally not a huge fan.
No clue of the authenticity of the menu, but interior, service and atmosphere are great.
Great sichuan

Outrageously good. Get the dumplings.
The food was great and the workers are so nice.
Awesome food
Salty and tasty.
Perfect! Amazing food and very friendly staff
Incredibly delicious.
Uniquely satisfying ambiance and venue. Arguably the best Chinese food in the city.

The food was incredible.  No mincing words. Truly 5 stars. (Read about how they special source their soy sauce, I was drinking spoonfuls of it...) On top of the food being incredible: - Cocktail was equally incredible - Great service - Music was awesome - Even the little coconut candy they give with the bill was delicious.  Check my review history - I don’t leave reviews really but was just so pleased with the experience.

Incredible food!! Some of the best soup dumplings I’ve ever had. Definitely recommend it!

Pretty good prix fixe deal for a dim sum and entree dish which is good for sharing.
My favorite spot to eat in Williamsburg, so damn good!

This place is great for groups. We found ourselves ordering everything on the menu just to get a taste! The options are thoughtful creative, but it still feels like your eating comfort food - the best of both worlds. The atmosphere is reminiscent of a cozy speakeasy.
Great food!

A step back in time in a historic facility. Lots of castle like architecture. The bathroom is a trip down a spiral stone staircase. Terrific tour and yummy tastings. Bring money. You’ll want to walk away with a bottle or two.
This was a really great place with amazing Chinese Food, it was a really amazing the service was great and the menu had all of my favorites. I had a great time and left full.
The food was ok, and the atmosphere nice.

Could possibly be the best Chinese food I’ve ever had. Try everything.
Tasty food and cocktail. Great vibe.  A little packed , but in general a very pleasant place to din in .

Best Chinese food I've had in a long time.  Make sure to let the waiter know if you want things not spicy because some items, like the Dan Dan Mian noodles, while very delicious, was incredibly spicy. I had the soup dumplings, soy braised crispy pork belly, dry fried long bean, sesame noodles, spring rolls, and crispy garlic chicken.  For those who don't consume pork, read the menu carefully. You may find it in a dish you wouldn't normally expect, such as the green beans. Everything was phenomenal, including the sweet chili cabbage that is complimentary and starts off your meal. I would highly recommend this place.
Great service

First off, place is cool. Like. New. York. Cool. We get there, at like, 17:30, and find out, there is like, only one table, that really, can fit does humans. It's only a little busy. But then. The ceaseless and unending march of entropy. Unexaminable on a local level, it's effect at the macro scale marches forth.by 5:50 the place was full to busting. As I said, this place was cool, so reservations were not the kind of 1950s bullshirt that was going to be allowed here. Anyways, drinks and food were good and waiter was waiting the correct amount. Come here and get the soup dumplings.

Absolutely love it!

Really delicious, gourmet Chinese dishes - akin to "real" Chinese food you might get in Chinatown or, indeed, China. We tried the soup dumplings, mock eel (don't let the name put you off - it was probably the highlight), and a couple of noodle dishes. This was plenty of food for three people - the bill came to around $100 with drinks. The vibe of the place is very Williamsburg... so unpretentious that it somehow manages to be a bit pretentious, but equally charming. The staff were genuinely friendly and warm, and helpful when it came to questions about the menu. The service was quick, too. Cocktails were fantastic as well!
We love spicy food! They have it! Chicken Kung Po is my favorite and it's a  real masterpiece!

The oyster mushrooms are standout - they are lightly crispy, kind of tempura style, and they have this dry spice (Sichuan peppercorn?) that is addictive. Long beans are also seared perfectly and have lots of soy umami. Go from 5-7 for a dinner deal!
Great food, the service was good. Would recommend this place to friends.
Great fun atmosphere and food. If you are around, def pay a visit.
Best soup dumplings around
Really great dim sum. Delicious soup dumplings. Scallion Pancakes! Pork! Noodles! And the cocktail was fantastic! Would definitely recommend. Cozy as well.

Love this place! Went there several times..One of the best restaurants in NYC. Great food, big portions, good atmosphere. Unbelievalbe value for DimSum menu (before 7:00 weekday only). Make sure you book in advance.  Crispy pork belly, radish cake, ants climbing on a tree..yum
So yummy! Big portions, get as much as you can and share everything... and if you cant finish they have cute to go boxes!
Consistently delicious food. If you go before 7:30 you can do the dim sum menu that is much cheaper than ordering one off dishes.
Fried rice is very tasty

Went into dinner thinking it’d be “white people’s Chinese food” (sorry but with a Chinese mom I tend to be judgey). Was way happily surprised with the dank shrimp toast and many mushroom noodles. Updated but authentic. So good. Would definitely recommend!
Phenomenal dining experience, 11/10. Great private dining room, GREAT sauce.
Very nice and good tasty

Love this place! Highly recommend for friends dinner, dinner for two. Lots to share! Get the mock eel, the longbeans, many mushroom noodle, the walnuts! Pretty much everything!

Take out review: they do a great job packaging the food for take out with the sauces separate even for the peanut noodles. Not too oily which is my main complaint with similar restaurant. Lots of character and fun in the dishes

Really great and authentic Asian food. The place is beautiful and modern and the staff helpful and friendly. Get more than one dish for everyone and share. The more people the better as you can try more things. But even as a couple we had a great food experience and we will definitely go again. The dan dan noodles are a little spicy, but still delicious. The vegetable dishes were all different and so tasty.

Before coming here you have to set your expectations especially if you are Chinese or know Chinese cuisine well. This isn’t Flushing, so of course you will get Chinese food made for the Williamsburg crowd. So no taking your Ah Mah or Poh Poh here, bring your Gwai Low friends instead. I brought one from upstate.  With that said, this place serves excellent food! I really enjoyed their eggplant and the tea smoked duck served with pancakes. Because we were just two people I could try the mushroom noodles which I wanted. The pork is sourced from Heritage farms making me more comfortable with eating it. Our server was very nice and attentive.
Gotta say I ordered dumps from this place which is generally a sus move but fully the best dumps I’ve ever had in my life!
Fastest service i have ever seen. Amazing quality into the food
By far the best Chinese food I’ve ever had in New York, actually the best Chinese food I’ve ever had anywhere including China.
The longbeans and aubergine dishes were amazing
Authentic Chinese food. great quality general tso chicken and seafood. My family enjoyed our visit.

My favourite Chinese place! Absolutely epic pork soup dumplings, don't forget to order them. All the dumplings are good, but the chicken is better than the long pork ones. The mushroom noodles are great, and so are the dan dan noodles. What to say, everything we have ordered has been good and I'm on a slow but steady mission to try everything on their menu! We waited an hour for a table the first time and it was worth the wait, and I'm not sure I've ever said that before! Will recommend highly!
Fresh hot delicious food and great service
best, most consistent meal around, and totally fair prices. Even went there for Christmas last year. A+, would recommend.
Delicious. Modern take on OG Chinese dishes.
Casual but refined atmosphere, GREAT food and service. Regularly crave the radish cakes.
Good Chinese fusion food, I really liked it, try anything you won't regret it
Amazing Chinese food in an unassuming spot. A surprising amount of vegan options and the waitress we had was super knowledgeable and made great suggestions. Def a spot you should check out!
Great feels. Great smells. Great food.
Incredible food, great vibe. Don’t miss the wok seared long dumpling and Hong king noodle. Its almost as good when delivering.
Absolutely phenomenal place for dumplings!

Food is mediocre and not spicy at all. Drinks are solid. Come for the drinks, not the food.

#FoodieBrad I’ll start by saying. 👏.... 👏 .... 👏  (slow clap) Order the chicken dumplings and green bean dish. Must try is the Dan Dan noodle. The food here is definitely well cooked and put together. The ambiance is a bit romantic but the overall environment is amazing. I loved the food....I must go back!

Surprisingly delicious Chinese food at this completely unremarkable location. There's a sweet little patio bar in the back, and two different dining areas in the main restaurant area. I appreciate that the food came out in waves as soon as it was ready rather than all at once since we were all sharing it anyway.

Great place to dine. Food is delicious and well cook. Staff is friendly and great service. Would come back anytime 🙂
Nice mixture of noodles and Dim Sum. Friendly service and nice pace to the food.
Great Chinese. Fun restaurant that is perfect for sharing.
Great cocktails, great staff and food is really good! Very good soup dumplings 👌🏽
Fried long beans are insanely good, so was everything else.

best Chinese i have had in a long time. make sure you book in advance and make sure to try as many dishes as possible. an fyi for the dessert lovers: they don’t serve desserts. don’t worry, you’ll feel fully satisfied without it!
Best Chinese American food by far
Best Chinese east of the Mississippi

Make a reservation.  This place was caught up in controversy after a racist review was published calling this white-owned restaurant the best Chinese restaurant in the city while disparaging Chinese and Chinese-American owned and operated Chinese restaurants that have been open and serving great food in this city for generations. Kings County Imperial didn't deserve to be caught in the middle of that nonsense, and nobody should let that color their judgment of the restaurant itself.  The food here is excellent. We didn't have a bad dish all night. The noodles, the pork belly, the soup dumplings, the pan-seared long dumplings, the dry fried long beans (!!!), the spring rolls, the mapo dofu...everything was incredibly delicious, with complex, exciting flavor combinations. We had a wonderful and helpful server, prompt service all night long, and just an overall excellent dinner.  The chairs are incredibly uncomfortable, so don't plan on sticking around too long. They're "eat and GTFO" chairs. Would be nice if they invested in more comfortable chairs, but they probably won't because they are trying to turn tables.  I will also echo that the cocktails are comparatively weak. My julep was mostly club soda. Decent wines available though!  Seriously excellent food and service. Go.
Spicy dan dan noodles will blow your mind! I'm lucky this place delivers, it's some of the best noodles around.
This staff are snobs and very off putting.  Luckily the food is INCREDIBLE.  Don’t know why the staff acts like you’re their uninvited guest though....

I can not believe that it took me so long to come here! Staff is great, good is fantastic.  I can't get the mock-eel out of my mind! I not even a vegetarian., but hope to be back next week to try some more dishes. The Brussels rocked too!

Two words: Soup Dumplings. Sit at the bar if you can, and always consider the specials, the magic mushroom noodles were the best to date. Interesting cocktails and good beer menu. Copper Street noodles, dan dan, and ants climbing up a tree are all great picks.

I have a new favorite Chinese restaurant and it’s called Kings County Imperial. Everything was delicious. Hands down the best hot and sour soup I’ve ever tried. Normally after I eat Chinese food I feel hungover. Not after Kings Imperial. The green beans are a must every time. Their dumplings are out of this world too. My favorite are the ribs, the duck and the ants climbing on a tree. Make a reservation in advance as this place books up quickly. Sometimes I’ll arrive without a reservation, put my name down, then go to Union Pool for some drinks until they call me. This 5 star rating is a no brainer.
